![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1578252923112-QRSOVYJIJGBSOZN4BHC8/image-asset.jpeg)

It is an abosulte joy to finally review the masterpiece that is Doom Patrol Season 1. From Extra-Dimensional Donkeys to Danny the Street, this series manages to pack every episode with heart, humor and spectacle in a way we've never seen before. When their leader The Chief is kidnapped by an omniscient prankster with a flair for narration, no stone gets unturned and everyone (including the delightful Brendan Fraser as Robotman) turns in stellar performances, as the show begs the question...What is a hero? If you were on the fence, let our pure praise tip you over the edge as we talk all things Doom Patrol in this spoiler-filled extravaganza about finding yourself, accepting your flaws, and changing your story!  
  
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience, and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the one stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
